:INFO
What Makes Bone Broth Different
Bone broth is simmered far longer than a standard stock, typically 12 to 24 hours \
for chicken bones and 24 to 48 hours for beef bones. This extended cooking time \
dissolves collagen from connective tissue and cartilage into gelatin, giving the \
finished broth a rich body that sets firm when refrigerated. Roasting the bones \
first adds deep flavor through the Maillard reaction.

